### Demo: humao REST Client - Microsoft Graph "who am I"
### Click "Send Request" above the GET line. Reply shows up in a side panel.

@graphBase = https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0
@token = PASTE-A-GRAPH-BEARER-HERE

### 1. Identity check
GET {{graphBase}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 2. Latest 5 sign-ins for current user (audit log)
GET {{graphBase}}/auditLogs/signIns?$top=5&$orderby=createdDateTime desc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Demo: Defender XDR Advanced Hunting via API
### POST a query and get JSON back. Replace tenant + token first.

@xdr = https://api.security.microsoft.com/api/advancedhunting/run
@xdrToken = PASTE-A-DEFENDER-API-TOKEN-HERE

### 3. Run a KQL hunt against your tenant
POST {{xdr}}
Authorization: Bearer {{xdrToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Query": "DeviceProcessEvents | where Timestamp > ago(1d) | where FileName =~ 'rundll32.exe' | take 5"
}
